By now, we can all agree that movie premieres are arguably one of the biggest fashion events in Lagos year on year. With the rapid rise of elaborate themes, celebrities and all-round premiere goers are forced to return to their creative boards and show up on the red carpet only in the best interpretations of the theme, which then go on to set Instagram comment sections and DMs on fire, filled with heated arguments about who looks good and who just wasn’t prepared. The stars are currently showing us yet again how it’s done with their Instagram posts from the EbonyLife TV‘s new movie Your Excellency premiere at the newly unveiled EbonyLife Place. All snatched and elegant, this is your first look from Your Excellency premiere. Don’t forget to check back for the best-dressed list from the event on Monday morning. @mimionalaja @inidimaokojie @ebuka @tokemakinwa @moabudu @sharonooja @iamtonitones @funkejenifaakindele @omawonder @lamide_a @tallulahglossy @officialosas @marcydolapooni @orekagodis @denolagrey @ekuedewor @the_vimbai @officialwaje @iam_ikeonyema @pelumi_shittu @lalaakindoju @theonlychigul The post First Photos: Lala Akindoju, Toke Makinwa, Denola Grey, Ini Dima Okojie, Mo Abudu at the Premiere of “Your Excellency” appeared first on BellaNaija – Showcasing Africa to the world. Read today!. Source: Bella Naija One of Nollywood’s most anticipated movies for 2019, “Love is War” premieres tonight and we are excited. The Omoni Oboli directed movie which will be out in cinemas from September 27, stars an impressive list of actors including Richard Mofe-Damijo, Jide Kosoko, Akin Lewis, Bimbo Manuel, Toke Makinwa, Shaffy Bello,… September 23, 2019 In "Entertainment" Toke Makinwa was the belle of the ball at the Elite Model Look Nigeria 2017 wearing a dress by Gert-Johan Coetzee Hello guys! So, this weekend was packed with lots of glam events – from weddings to a movie premiere and the Elite Model Look Nigeria 2017 – and as… October 9, 2017 In "News" Funke Akindele Bell